{"#tail": " shall prescribe such regulations as are necessary to carry out this section.", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Secretary of State", "@entity-id": "1900"}, "#text": "The "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(d)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "Regulatory authority"}, "#text": "\n        ", "@id": "id75b5af2eb09e4268859122e9842dc434"}], "#text": "\n      ", "@id": "id147db0527f044b36976471994eba48fe"}, {"#tail": "\n    ", "enum": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "5."}, "header": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "Financial measures"}, "subsection": [{"#tail": "\n      ", "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(a)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "Freezing of assets"}, "paragraph": [{"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n        ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": [{"#tail": " shall exercise all powers granted by the ", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "President", "@entity-id": "1100"}, {"#tail": " of this Act if such property and  interests in property are in the United States, come within the  United States, or are or come within the possession or control  of a United States person.", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "section 3(a)", "@value": "Global Human Rights Accountability Act/s:3/ss:a", "@proposed": "true"}], "#text": "The ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity": [{"#tail": " (except that the requirements of ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": [{"#tail": " (", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "International Emergency Economic Powers Act", "@value": "International Emergency Economic Powers Act"}, {"#tail": ")", "@entity-type": "uscode", "#text": "50  U.S.C. 1701 et seq.", "@value": "usc/50/1701/etseq"}], "@entity-type": "law-citation", "#text": "\n              "}, {"#tail": " shall not apply) to the extent  necessary to freeze and prohibit all transactions in all  property and interests in property of a foreign person on the  list required by ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": " (", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "section  202 of such Act", "@value": "International Emergency Economic Powers Act/s:202"}, "@entity-type": "law-citation", "#text": "\n              ", "external-xref": {"#tail": ")", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": "\n              ", "@entity-type": "uscode", "#text": "50 U.S.C. 1701", "@value": "usc/50/1701"}, "@parsable-cite": "usc/50/1701", "#text": "\n                ", "@legal-doc": "usc"}}]}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(1)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "In general"}, "#text": "\n          ", "@id": "idcc43e8538812424ea3024af152797ad0"}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n        ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": [{"#tail": " shall not apply to foreign persons included on the classified annex  under ", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "Paragraph (1)", "@value": "Global Human Rights Accountability Act/s:5/ss:a/p:1", "@proposed": "true"}, {"#tail": " if the ", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "section 3(c)(2)", "@value": "Global Human Rights Accountability Act/s:3/ss:c/p:2", "@proposed": "true"}, {"#tail": " determines that such an  exception is vital to the national security interests of the  United States.", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "President", "@entity-id": "1100"}], "#text": "\n            "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(2)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "Exception"}, "#text": "\n          ", "@id": "id3555c9d8a7a6436ebcb67e5b84075b97"}], "#text": "\n        ", "@id": "id04615219ed0f4f93b8b6aa24487e59cc"}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n        ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": [{"#tail": " may waive the application of  ", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Secretary of the Treasury", "@entity-id": "2000"}, {"#tail": " if the ", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "subsection (a)", "@value": "Global Human Rights Accountability Act/s:5/ss:a", "@proposed": "true"}, {"#tail": "\u2014", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Secretary", "@entity-id": "2000"}], "#text": "The "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(b)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "Waiver for national security interests"}, "paragraph": [{"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "determines that such a waiver is in the  national security interests of the  United States; and"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(1)"}, "@id": "id7CA84B9ACBB44CB8B98B7A7154E2670D", "#text": "\n          "}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "not later than 15 days before granting the waiver, provides to the  appropriate congressional committees notice of, and a justification for,  the waiver."}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(2)"}, "@id": "id6CED9D80D46545A2A415B076B92AFE46", "#text": "\n          "}], "#text": "\n        ", "@id": "idc608c393f2f949bb82ecebf74cca1ad4"}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(c)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "Enforcement"}, "paragraph": [{"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n        ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": " of that section.", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "subsection (a)", "@value": "International Emergency Economic Powers Act/s:206/ss:a"}, "#text": "A person that violates, attempts to violate, conspires to violate, or causes a violation of this section or  any regulation, license, or order issued to carry out this  section shall be subject to the penalties set forth in  ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity": {"#tail": " to the same  extent as a person that commits an unlawful act described in  ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": [{"#tail": " and ", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "subsections (b)", "@value": "International Emergency Economic Powers Act/s:206/ss:b"}, {"#tail": " (", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "(c) of section 206 of the International  Emergency Economic Powers Act", "@value": "International Emergency Economic Powers Act/s:206/ss:c"}], "@entity-type": "law-citation", "#text": "\n              ", "external-xref": {"#tail": ")", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": "\n              ", "@entity-type": "uscode", "#text": "50 U.S.C. 1705", "@value": "usc/50/1705"}, "@parsable-cite": "usc/50/1705", "#text": "\n                ", "@legal-doc": "usc"}}}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(1)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "Penalties"}, "#text": "\n          ", "@id": "idc36754157ad545b1896f9bba32d9316f"}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n        ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": [{"#tail": "  shall prescribe regulations requiring each  financial institution that is a United States person and has  within its possession or control assets that are property or  interests in property of a foreign person on the list required by  ", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Secretary of the Treasury", "@entity-id": "2000"}, {"#tail": " to certify to the ", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "section 3(a)", "@value": "Global Human Rights Accountability Act/s:3/ss:a", "@proposed": "true"}, {"#tail": " that, to the best  of the knowledge of the financial institution, the financial  institution has frozen all  assets within the possession or control of the financial  institution that are required to be frozen pursuant to  ", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Secretary", "@entity-id": "2000"}, {"#tail": ".", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "subsection (a)", "@value": "Global Human Rights Accountability Act/s:5/ss:a", "@proposed": "true"}], "#text": "Not later than 120 days after the  date of the enactment of this Act, the "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(2)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "Requirements for financial 